<subSubSection pageId="30" pageNumber="31" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="30.[189,494,903,930]" box="[189,494,903,930]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,494,903,930]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,494,903,930]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Distribution and habitat</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="30.[189,1398,950,1012]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
The Palearctic region, except in the northern parts. In 
<collectingRegion box="[854,955,950,976]" country="Portugal" name="Madeira" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Madeira</collectingRegion>
, this species is found in 
<taxonomicName authority="Trin. ex Steud." authorityName="Steud." class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Phragmites" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="australis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Phragmites australis</emphasis>
Trin. ex Steud.
</taxonomicName>
in the only tide lagoon of the island, which is located on the southern coast.
</paragraph>
